<h3 id="a-passion-for-technology">A Passion for Technology</h3>

<p>Without getting into too much detail, being a Technical Writer/Documentation Engineer means that I need to be able to adopt emerging technologies. Over the past year, one of the more prominent trends I have witnessed is for static sites to be used to maintain technical documentation.</p>

<p>So, I figured what better way to understand static sites than to use Jekyll, a static site generator, to build my own documentation portal?</p>

<h3 id="growing-need-for-an-online-portfolio">Growing Need for an Online Portfolio</h3>

<p>Put simply, sending a barrage of Google docs and PDFs seemed unprofessional, and sending screenshots of web pages featuring my content felt lazy. So, I decided that Jekyll/Github Pages would be a fun way to showcase some of the projects Iâ€™ve recently worked on.</p>

